[[File:Carbon Dust Skull.jpg|thumb|Carbon dust illustration]]'''Carbon dust''' is an artistic technique in which carbon dust is applied to a prepared surface via dry brushes.  Highlights may be painted on or scratched out later in the process.  Dust is prepared by rubbing [[carbon]] [[pencil]]s against an abrasive surface, such as a metal file.  The technique was popularized by [[Max Brödel]] (1870-1941) and became widely used among [[Medical illustration|medical]] and [[:Category:Scientific illustrators|scientific illustrators]] in the twentieth century.

